{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalNePropStep\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalNePropStep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ne</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mkNeProof</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.SimpM\">SimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.SimpM\">SimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.Step\">Step</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `evalPropStep`, but specialized for `@Ne.{u} α a b`. When the values differ, calls\n`mkNeProof` to build a proof of `a ≠ b`. When equal, uses `eq_false (not_not_intro rfl)`\nwhich requires no kernel evaluation.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalNePropStep","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Lean.Meta.Simp.evalNePropStep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.lean#L44-L61"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalEqPropStep\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalEqPropStep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">eq</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mkNeProof</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.SimpM\">SimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.SimpM\">SimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.Step\">Step</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `evalPropStep`, but specialized for `@Eq.{u} α a b`. When the values are equal, uses\n`eq_true rfl` which requires no kernel evaluation. When different, calls `mkNeProof` to build\na proof of `a ≠ b`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalEqPropStep","kind":"def","line":27,"name":"Lean.Meta.Simp.evalEqPropStep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.lean#L27-L42"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalPropStep\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Simp</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalPropStep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">result</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.SimpM\">SimpM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.Step\">Step</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `result` be the result of evaluating proposition `p`, return a `.done` step where\nthe resulting expression is `True`(`False`) if `result is `true`(`false`), and the\nproof is uses `Decidable p` and the auxiliary theorems `eq_true_of_decide`/`eq_false_of_decide`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Simp.evalPropStep","kind":"def","line":15,"name":"Lean.Meta.Simp.evalPropStep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Simp/BuiltinSimprocs/Util.lean#L15-L25"}}],"imports":["Lean.Meta.Tactic.Simp.Simproc"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Meta.Tactic.Simp.BuiltinSimprocs.Util"}